		<part id="how-what-why">
			<title>From <q>How</q> to <q>What</q> to <q>Why</q></title>
			<slide id="api-hype-curve">
				<title>Watch out for Disappointment</title>
				<img src="hype-curve-unicorn.png" style=" width : 90% ; height : 70% ; object-fit : contain ; margin : 0% 4% 0% 4% ; "/>
			</slide>
			<slide id="how">
				<title><q>How are things going?</q></title>
				<ul>
					<li>Initial conversations often start with technical problems or goals</li>
					<li>Walk <q>up</q> the chain from implementation to plan to strategy</li>
					<li>Are we building <em>a product that will be a useful digital product?</em></li>
					<ul>
						<li><em>Every API is a product</em> because it can be used in digital value chains</li>
					</ul>
				</ul>
			</slide>
			<slide id="what">
				<title><q>What are you trying to achieve?</q></title>
				<ul>
					<li>APIs never are the end goal</li>
					<li>Digital transformation is much more than just APIs</li>
					<ul>
						<li>You need to build the <em>right APIs</em></li>
						<li>You need to <em>manage them right</em></li>
						<li>The organization needs to be capable to leverage them</li>
					</ul>
				</ul>
			</slide>
			<slide id="why">
				<title><q>Why are you trying to achieve this?</q></title>
				<ul>
					<li><q href="https://hbr.org/2020/05/good-leadership-is-about-communicating-why">Good Leadership Is About Communicating <q>Why</q></q></li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
			<slide id="deep-dive">
				<title>Strategy Deep Dive</title>
				<blockquote><q>Vision without execution is hallucination.</q> (<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thomas_Edison">Thomas Edison</a>)</blockquote>
			</slide>
		</part>
		<part id="understanding">
			<title>Understanding: What Do You Mean?</title>
			<slide id="wittgenstein">
				<title>The Meaning of Words</title>
				<blockquote><q href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philosophical_Investigations#Meaning_is_use">The meaning of a word is its use in the language.</q> (<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ludwig_Wittgenstein">Ludwig Wittgenstein</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philosophical_Investigations">Philosophical Investigations</a>, 1953)</blockquote>
				<ul>
					<li>There is no <em>abstract meaning</em> that a word then <q>references</q></li>
					<li>Communication establishes the meaning and makes the word usable and useful</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
			<slide id="big-five">
				<title>The Big Five</title>
				<ul>
					<li>API Strategy → How does it relate to <q>other strategy</q>?</li>
					<li>API Management → Narrow and technical or full product lifecycle?</li>
					<li>Platforms → Technical foundations or the business model?</li>
					<li>Integration → Loose coupling or tight coupling?</li>
					<li>Open API → Open APIs for general consumption or OAI?</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
		</part>
